# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:69
msgid "-A-"
msgstr "-A-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:70
msgid "A-Roll:"
msgstr "A-Roll:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:71
msgid "The Principal video that is usually someone speaking."
msgstr "Video utama yang biasanya menampilkan seseorang berbicara."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:72
msgid "Aliasing:"
msgstr "Aliasing:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:73
msgid ""
"The undesirable jagged or stair-stepped appearance of angled lines in an "
"image, graphic, or text."
msgstr ""
"Penampilan bergerigi atau bertangga yang tidak diinginkan pada garis miring "
"dalam gambar, grafik, atau teks."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:74
msgid "Alpha:"
msgstr "Alpha:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:75
msgid ""
"Alpha blending is a convex combination of two colors allowing for "
"transparency effects in computer graphics.  The value of alpha in the color "
"code ranges from 0.0 to 1.0, where 0.0 represents a fully transparent color, "
"and 1.0 represents a fully opaque color."
msgstr ""
"Alpha blending adalah kombinasi konveks dari dua warna yang memungkinkan "
"efek transparansi dalam grafik komputer. Nilai alpha dalam kode warna "
"berkisar dari 0.0 hingga 1.0, di mana 0.0 mewakili warna yang sepenuhnya "
"transparan, dan 1.0 mewakili warna yang sepenuhnya buram."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:76
msgid "Alpha Channel:"
msgstr "Saluran Alpha:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:77
msgid ""
"An alpha channel is a channel in an image or movie clip that controls the "
"opacity region."
msgstr ""
"Saluran alpha adalah saluran dalam gambar atau klip film yang mengontrol "
"wilayah opasitas."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:78
msgid "Ambient Noise:"
msgstr "Suara Latar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:79
msgid "Ambient noise is background noise specific to the shooting location."
msgstr ""
"Suara latar adalah suara latar belakang yang spesifik untuk lokasi "
"pengambilan gambar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:80
msgid "Animation:"
msgstr "Animasi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:81
msgid ""
"The technique of making inanimate objects or drawings appear to move in "
"motion pictures or computer graphics."
msgstr ""
"Teknik membuat objek mati atau gambar tampak bergerak dalam film atau grafik "
"komputer."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:82
msgid "Anti-Aliasing:"
msgstr "Anti-Aliasing:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:83
msgid ""
"Anti-aliasing is a process for smoothing jagged lines in an image.  Anti-"
"aliasing can also mean a method of filtering out erroneous frequencies in an "
"audio signal."
msgstr ""
"Anti-aliasing adalah proses untuk menghaluskan garis bergerigi dalam gambar. "
"Anti-aliasing juga dapat berarti metode penyaringan frekuensi salah dalam "
"sinyal audio."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:84
msgid "Artifact:"
msgstr "Artefak:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:85
msgid ""
"An artifact is undesired data in an image because of digital processing."
msgstr ""
"Artefak adalah data yang tidak diinginkan dalam gambar akibat pemrosesan "
"digital."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:86
msgid "Aspect Ratio:"
msgstr "Rasio Aspek:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:87
msgid ""
"The ratio of width to height in a flat surface or 2-dimensional abstract "
"construction, such as an image, video, character, or pixel.  The standard "
"ratios for NTSC SD videos are 4:3 (or 1.33:1) and HD 16:9 (or 1.77:1).  The "
"most common aspect ratios for motion pictures are 1.85:1 and 2.35:1."
msgstr ""
"Rasio lebar terhadap tinggi pada permukaan datar atau konstruksi abstrak 2 "
"dimensi, seperti gambar, video, karakter, atau piksel. Rasio standar untuk "
"video NTSC SD adalah 4:3 (atau 1,33:1) dan HD 16:9 (atau 1,77:1). Rasio "
"aspek paling umum untuk film adalah 1,85:1 dan 2,35:1."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:88
msgid "ATSC:"
msgstr "ATSC:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:89
msgid ""
"ATSC is a digital broadcast standard that replaced the older analog NTSC "
"standard.  The standard covers both standard and high-definition formats."
msgstr ""
"ATSC adalah standar siaran digital yang menggantikan standar analog NTSC "
"yang lama. Standar ini mencakup format standar dan definisi tinggi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:91
msgid "Audio Sample Rate:"
msgstr "Laju Sampel Audio:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:91
msgid ""
"The number of samples taken per second to reproduce audio digitally.  The "
"higher the sample rate, the higher the quality of the digital audio.  A rate "
"of 44,100 samples per second produces CD-quality audio and captures the "
"range of human hearing."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah sampel yang diambil per detik untuk mereproduksi audio secara "
"digital. Semakin tinggi laju sampel, semakin tinggi kualitas audio digital. "
"Laju 44.100 sampel per detik menghasilkan audio kualitas CD dan menangkap "
"rentang pendengaran manusia."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:96
msgid "-B-"
msgstr "-B-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:97
msgid "B-roll:"
msgstr "B-roll:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:98
msgid ""
"B-roll is supplemental footage that provides supporting details and greater "
"flexibility when editing video.  Common examples include the footage used to "
"cut away from an interview or news report to help tell the story."
msgstr ""
"B-roll adalah rekaman tambahan yang memberikan detail pendukung dan "
"fleksibilitas lebih saat menyunting video. Contoh umum termasuk rekaman yang "
"digunakan untuk memotong dari wawancara atau laporan berita untuk membantu "
"menceritakan kisah."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:99
msgid "Bit:"
msgstr "Bit:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:100
msgid ""
"The elementary unit for digital storage.  A BIT can be either a 1 (one) or a "
"0 (zero)."
msgstr ""
"Unit dasar untuk penyimpanan digital. Bit dapat berupa 1 (satu) atau 0 (nol)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:101
msgid "Bit Depth:"
msgstr "Kedalaman Bit:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:102
msgid ""
"In digital graphics and video, bit depth indicates the number of colors an "
"image can display.  A high-contrast (no gray tones) black and white image is "
"1bit, meaning it can be off or on, black or white.  As bit depth increases, "
"more colors become available.  24-bit color allows for displays of millions "
"of colors.  Similarly, in digital audio, bit depth indicates the number of "
"bits per sample.  The higher the number, the better the sound quality."
msgstr ""
"Dalam grafik dan video digital, kedalaman bit menunjukkan jumlah warna yang "
"dapat ditampilkan oleh sebuah gambar. Gambar hitam putih dengan kontras "
"tinggi (tanpa nada abu-abu) adalah 1 bit, artinya bisa mati atau hidup, "
"hitam atau putih. Semakin tinggi kedalaman bit, semakin banyak warna yang "
"tersedia. Warna 24-bit memungkinkan tampilan jutaan warna. Demikian pula, "
"dalam audio digital, kedalaman bit menunjukkan jumlah bit per sampel. "
"Semakin tinggi angkanya, semakin baik kualitas suara."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:103
msgid "Bitrate:"
msgstr "Bitrate:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:104
msgid ""
"The frequency at which bits (binary digits) pass a given physical or "
"metaphorical point, measured in bps (bits per second).  For every second in "
"the video, the Bit Rate, or Data Rate, is the amount of data used each "
"second.  The bitrate, in Kilobits per second, can be variable or constant."
msgstr ""
"Frekuensi di mana bit (digit biner) melewati titik fisik atau metaforis "
"tertentu, diukur dalam bps (bit per detik). Untuk setiap detik dalam video, "
"Bitrate atau Data Rate adalah jumlah data yang digunakan setiap detik. "
"Bitrate, dalam Kilobit per detik, dapat bersifat variabel atau konstan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:105
msgid "Blue Screen:"
msgstr "Layar Biru:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:106
msgid ""
"A blue screen is a blue background that the subject stands in front of that "
"the computer later replaces with another background in post-production.  See "
"also blue screen compositing and green screen."
msgstr ""
"Layar biru adalah latar belakang biru yang menjadi tempat subjek berdiri dan "
"kemudian digantikan oleh komputer dengan latar belakang lain dalam pasca-"
"produksi. Lihat juga komposit layar biru dan layar hijau."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:108
msgid "Blue Screen Compositing:"
msgstr "Komposit Layar Biru:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:108
msgid ""
"The process of making all blue elements in an image transparent and placing "
"a different background underneath."
msgstr ""
"Proses membuat semua elemen biru dalam gambar menjadi transparan dan "
"menempatkan latar belakang berbeda di bawahnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:113
msgid "-C-"
msgstr "-C-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:114
msgid "Capture:"
msgstr "Tangkap:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:115
msgid ""
"The process of transferring source video from a camcorder or tape deck to a "
"computer.  If the source video is analog, the capture process converts the "
"video to digital."
msgstr ""
"Proses mentransfer video sumber dari camcorder atau tape deck ke komputer. "
"Jika video sumber adalah analog, proses penangkapan mengubah video menjadi "
"digital."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:116
msgid "Channel:"
msgstr "Saluran:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:117
msgid ""
"A channel is one of several grayscale components used to make up a color "
"image.  Red, green, and blue channels make up RGB images, with an optional "
"alpha channel for transparency."
msgstr ""
"Saluran adalah salah satu dari beberapa komponen skala abu-abu yang "
"digunakan untuk membentuk gambar berwarna. Saluran merah, hijau, dan biru "
"membentuk gambar RGB, dengan saluran alfa opsional untuk transparansi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:118
msgid "Chromakey:"
msgstr "Chromakey:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:119
msgid ""
"Chromakey is a method of creating transparency in a video source by "
"selecting a specific \"key color\" to create an alpha matte.  It is "
"frequently used on news programs to display weather graphics behind talent "
"and for visual effects compositing."
msgstr ""
"Chromakey adalah metode membuat transparansi dalam sumber video dengan "
"memilih \"warna kunci\" tertentu untuk membuat matte alfa. Ini sering "
"digunakan dalam program berita untuk menampilkan grafik cuaca di belakang "
"presenter dan untuk komposit efek visual."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:120
msgid "Clip:"
msgstr "Klip:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:121
msgid ""
"A digitized or captured portion of video, audio, or both.  Clips are media "
"files added to the Timeline, usually part of a more extensive recording."
msgstr ""
"Bagian video, audio, atau keduanya yang telah didigitalkan atau ditangkap. "
"Klip adalah file media yang ditambahkan ke Timeline, biasanya bagian dari "
"rekaman yang lebih panjang."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:122
msgid "Codec:"
msgstr "Codec:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:123
msgid ""
"Codec is a video compression technology used to compress data in a video "
"file.  Codec stands for \"Compression Decompression.\" An example of a "
"popular codec is H.264."
msgstr ""
"Codec adalah teknologi kompresi video yang digunakan untuk mengompres data "
"dalam file video. Codec adalah singkatan dari \"Compression Decompression.\" "
"Contoh codec populer adalah H.264."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:124
msgid "Color Correction:"
msgstr "Koreksi Warna:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:125
msgid ""
"The process of altering the color of a video, especially one shot under less "
"than ideal conditions, such as low light."
msgstr ""
"Proses mengubah warna video, terutama yang diambil dalam kondisi kurang "
"ideal, seperti cahaya rendah."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:126
msgid "Compositing:"
msgstr "Kompositing:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:127
msgid ""
"Construction of a composite image by combining multiple images and other "
"elements."
msgstr ""
"Pembuatan gambar komposit dengan menggabungkan beberapa gambar dan elemen "
"lainnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:128
msgid "Coverage:"
msgstr "Coverage:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:129
msgid ""
"Coverage is the process of shooting additional footage and camera angles to "
"cover the action in the scene.  Coverage is so that the editor has a more "
"excellent range of choices when the film reaches the post-production stage."
msgstr ""
"Coverage adalah proses pengambilan gambar tambahan dan sudut kamera untuk "
"meliput aksi dalam adegan. Coverage bertujuan agar editor memiliki pilihan "
"yang lebih luas saat film mencapai tahap pascaproduksi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:130
msgid "Compression:"
msgstr "Kompresi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:131
msgid ""
"The process of reducing data, such as in an audio or video file, into a form "
"that requires less space."
msgstr ""
"Proses mengurangi data, seperti dalam file audio atau video, menjadi bentuk "
"yang memerlukan ruang lebih sedikit."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:132
msgid "Crop Factor:"
msgstr "Faktor Crop:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:133
msgid ""
"Crop factor is a number (typically from 1.3-2.0) that represents the ratio "
"of a sensor's imaging area to that of a full-frame sensor.  Try multiplying "
"the focal length of your lens by your camera sensor's crop factor.  It gives "
"you the focal length for the lens/sensor combination."
msgstr ""
"Faktor crop adalah angka (biasanya dari 1,3-2,0) yang mewakili rasio area "
"pencitraan sensor terhadap sensor full-frame. Coba kalikan panjang fokus "
"lensa Anda dengan faktor crop sensor kamera Anda. Ini memberi Anda panjang "
"fokus untuk kombinasi lensa/sensor."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:134
msgid "Crawl:"
msgstr "Crawl:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:135
msgid ""
"Crawl is a text effect where the text moves right-to-left (in the English-"
"speaking world)."
msgstr ""
"Crawl adalah efek teks di mana teks bergerak dari kanan ke kiri (dalam dunia "
"berbahasa Inggris)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:136
msgid "Cross-fade:"
msgstr "Cross-fade:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:137
msgid ""
"A cross-fade is a simultaneous fade-in of one audio or video source as "
"another fades out so that they overlap temporarily.  Also called a dissolve."
msgstr ""
"Cross-fade adalah perpindahan suara atau video di mana satu sumber memudar "
"masuk secara bersamaan saat sumber lain memudar keluar sehingga keduanya "
"tumpang tindih sementara. Juga disebut dissolve."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:138
msgid "Cut:"
msgstr "Cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:139
msgid "A cut is an instantaneous change from one shot to another."
msgstr "Cut adalah perubahan instan dari satu bidikan ke bidikan lain."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:140
msgid "Cut-in (Insert Shot):"
msgstr "Cut-in (Insert Shot):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:141
msgid ""
"It is a type of shot that most often shows the objects the subject is in "
"contact with or manipulating.  Cut-in shots are correspondingly helpful to b-"
"roll because they stray from the subject for a short time."
msgstr ""
"Ini adalah jenis bidikan yang paling sering menunjukkan objek yang sedang "
"disentuh atau dimanipulasi oleh subjek. Bidikan cut-in berguna sebagai b-"
"roll karena menjauh dari subjek untuk sementara waktu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:143
msgid "Cutting on Action:"
msgstr "Cutting on Action:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:143
msgid ""
"Cutting on action is a technique used to create a more interesting scene. "
"The concept is simple… when you cut in the middle of an action, it will "
"appear less jarring and more visual interesting."
msgstr ""
"Cutting on action adalah teknik yang digunakan untuk menciptakan adegan yang "
"lebih menarik. Konsepnya sederhana… saat Anda memotong di tengah aksi, itu "
"akan terlihat kurang mengganggu dan lebih menarik secara visual."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:148
msgid "-D-"
msgstr "-D-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:149
msgid "Data Rate:"
msgstr "Laju Data:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:150
msgid ""
"The amount of data moved over time (for example, 10 MB per second).  Often "
"used to describe a hard drive's ability to retrieve and deliver information."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah data yang dipindahkan selama waktu tertentu (misalnya, 10 MB per "
"detik). Sering digunakan untuk menggambarkan kemampuan hard drive dalam "
"mengambil dan mengirimkan informasi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:151
msgid "Denominator:"
msgstr "Penyebut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:152
msgid "The number or expression below the line in a fraction (such as 2 in ½)."
msgstr ""
"Angka atau ekspresi di bawah garis dalam sebuah pecahan (seperti 2 dalam ½)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:153
msgid "Digital Video:"
msgstr "Video Digital:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:154
msgid ""
"Digital video is an electronic representation of moving visual images "
"(video) in the form of encoded digital data.  In contrast, analog video "
"represents moving visual images with analog signals.  Digital video "
"comprises a series of digital images displayed in rapid succession."
msgstr ""
"Video digital adalah representasi elektronik dari gambar visual bergerak "
"(video) dalam bentuk data digital yang dikodekan. Sebaliknya, video analog "
"merepresentasikan gambar visual bergerak dengan sinyal analog. Video digital "
"terdiri dari serangkaian gambar digital yang ditampilkan secara berurutan "
"dengan cepat."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:155
msgid "Digitize:"
msgstr "Digitalkan:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:156
msgid "To convert analog video or audio to digital form."
msgstr "Mengubah video atau audio analog menjadi bentuk digital."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:158
msgid "Dissolve:"
msgstr "Dissolve:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:158
msgid ""
"Dissolve is an image transition effect where one picture gradually "
"disappears as another appears.  Also called a cross-fade."
msgstr ""
"Dissolve adalah efek transisi gambar di mana satu gambar perlahan menghilang "
"saat gambar lain muncul. Juga disebut cross-fade."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:163
msgid "-E-"
msgstr "-E-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:164
msgid "Editing:"
msgstr "Penyuntingan:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:165
msgid ""
"Editing is the process or result of selectively sequencing video and audio "
"clips into a new video file.  Typically involves reviewing raw footage and "
"transferring desired segments from source footage into a new predetermined "
"sequence."
msgstr ""
"Penyuntingan adalah proses atau hasil pengurutan selektif klip video dan "
"audio menjadi file video baru. Biasanya melibatkan peninjauan rekaman mentah "
"dan pemindahan segmen yang diinginkan dari rekaman sumber ke urutan baru "
"yang telah ditentukan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:166
msgid "Effect:"
msgstr "Efek:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:167
msgid ""
"Synthetic sounds and animations created in the digital domain applied to a "
"clip to change a specific parameter of video or audio.  Examples: the color "
"of a visual element or the reverb on an audio track."
msgstr ""
"Suara sintetis dan animasi yang dibuat dalam domain digital yang diterapkan "
"pada klip untuk mengubah parameter tertentu dari video atau audio. Contoh: "
"warna elemen visual atau reverb pada trek audio."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:168
msgid "Encode:"
msgstr "Encode:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:169
msgid ""
"To merge the individual video signals (for example, red, green, and blue) "
"into a combined signal, or to convert a video file to a different format "
"using a codec."
msgstr ""
"Menggabungkan sinyal video individual (misalnya, merah, hijau, dan biru) "
"menjadi sinyal gabungan, atau mengonversi file video ke format berbeda "
"menggunakan codec."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:171
msgid "Export:"
msgstr "Ekspor:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:171
msgid ""
"Export refers to the process of assembling your edited video project into a "
"single file that then plays back on its own, shared, or uploaded."
msgstr ""
"Ekspor mengacu pada proses menyusun proyek video yang telah diedit menjadi "
"satu file yang kemudian dapat diputar sendiri, dibagikan, atau diunggah."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:176
msgid "-F-"
msgstr "-F-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:177
msgid "Fade:"
msgstr "Fade:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:178
msgid ""
"A fade is the gradual diminishing or heightening of visual or audio "
"intensity.  Usage: fade-out, fade to black, fade-in, or fade up from black."
msgstr ""
"Fade adalah pengurangan atau peningkatan bertahap intensitas visual atau "
"audio. Penggunaan: fade-out, fade ke hitam, fade-in, atau fade naik dari "
"hitam."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:179
msgid "Fade-in:"
msgstr "Fade-in:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:180
msgid ""
"1.(n.) a shot that begins in total darkness and gradually lightens to full "
"brightness.  2. (v.) To gradually bring sound from inaudibility to the "
"required volume."
msgstr ""
"1.(n.) sebuah bidikan yang dimulai dalam kegelapan total dan secara bertahap "
"menjadi terang penuh. 2. (v.) Secara bertahap membawa suara dari tidak "
"terdengar ke volume yang diinginkan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:181
msgid "Fade-out:"
msgstr "Fade-out:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:182
msgid ""
"1.(n.) a shot that begins in full brightness and gradually dims to total "
"darkness.  2. (v.) To gradually bring sound from the required volume to "
"inaudibility."
msgstr ""
"1.(n.) sebuah bidikan yang dimulai dengan kecerahan penuh dan secara "
"bertahap meredup menjadi kegelapan total. 2. (v.) Secara bertahap membawa "
"suara dari volume yang diinginkan menjadi tidak terdengar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:183
msgid "Filter:"
msgstr "Filter:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:184
msgid ""
"A video filter is a software component that performs some operation on a "
"multimedia stream.  Multiple filters used in a chain, known as a filter "
"graph, are the process in which each filter receives input from its upstream "
"filter.  The filter graph processes the input and outputs the processed "
"video to its downstream filter."
msgstr ""
"Filter video adalah komponen perangkat lunak yang melakukan operasi pada "
"aliran multimedia. Beberapa filter yang digunakan secara berantai, dikenal "
"sebagai grafik filter, adalah proses di mana setiap filter menerima input "
"dari filter hulu. Grafik filter memproses input dan mengeluarkan video yang "
"telah diproses ke filter hilir."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:185
msgid "Final Cut:"
msgstr "Final Cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:186
msgid ""
"The final video production, assembled from high-quality clips, and ready for "
"export to the selected delivery media."
msgstr ""
"Produksi video akhir, disusun dari klip berkualitas tinggi, dan siap untuk "
"diekspor ke media pengiriman yang dipilih."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:187
msgid "Finishing:"
msgstr "Finishing:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:188
msgid ""
"The stage that brings together all assets of a piece.  Your output from this "
"stage is your master/sub-master."
msgstr ""
"Tahap yang menggabungkan semua aset dari sebuah karya. Output Anda dari "
"tahap ini adalah master/sub-master Anda."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:189
msgid "Footage:"
msgstr "Footage:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:190
msgid ""
"Derived from having feet of film, this is almost synonymous with video clips."
msgstr ""
"Berasal dari istilah 'feet of film', ini hampir sinonim dengan klip video."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:191
msgid "Frame:"
msgstr "Frame:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:192
msgid ""
"In filmmaking, video production, animation, and related fields, a frame is "
"one of the many still images which compose the complete moving picture."
msgstr ""
"Dalam pembuatan film, produksi video, animasi, dan bidang terkait, frame "
"adalah salah satu dari banyak gambar diam yang membentuk gambar bergerak "
"lengkap."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:193
msgid "Frames Per Second (fps):"
msgstr "Frame Per Detik (fps):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:194
msgid ""
"The number of frames played every second.  At 15 fps and lower, the human "
"eye can detect individual frames, causing the video to appear jerky."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah frame yang diputar setiap detik. Pada 15 fps dan lebih rendah, mata "
"manusia dapat mendeteksi frame individual, menyebabkan video terlihat patah-"
"patah."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:195
msgid "Frame Rate:"
msgstr "Kecepatan Frame:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:196
msgid ""
"Frame rate (expressed in frames per second or FPS) is the frequency (rate "
"expressed in Hz) at which consecutive images called frames appear on "
"display.  The term applies equally to film and video cameras, computer "
"graphics, and motion capture systems.  Common Frame Rate Examples: 24, 25, "
"29.97, 30, 50, 60."
msgstr ""
"Kecepatan frame (dinyatakan dalam frame per detik atau FPS) adalah frekuensi "
"(laju yang dinyatakan dalam Hz) di mana gambar berurutan yang disebut frame "
"muncul di layar. Istilah ini berlaku sama untuk kamera film dan video, "
"grafik komputer, dan sistem penangkap gerak. Contoh Kecepatan Frame Umum: "
"24, 25, 29,97, 30, 50, 60."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:198
msgid "Frequency:"
msgstr "Frekuensi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:198
msgid ""
"The number of audio cycles per second, expressed in hertz (Hz).  Frequency "
"determines the pitch of a sound."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah siklus audio per detik, dinyatakan dalam hertz (Hz). Frekuensi "
"menentukan nada suara."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:203
msgid "-G-"
msgstr "-G-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:204
msgid "Gamma:"
msgstr "Gamma:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:205
msgid ""
"A measurement of the intensity of mid-tones in an image.  Adjusting the "
"gamma adjusts the level of the mid-tones while leaving the blacks and whites "
"untouched."
msgstr ""
"Pengukuran intensitas nada tengah dalam sebuah gambar. Menyesuaikan gamma "
"mengatur tingkat nada tengah sambil membiarkan warna hitam dan putih tidak "
"berubah."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:206
msgid "GPU:"
msgstr "GPU:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:207
msgid ""
"Graphics processing unit.  A microprocessor with built-in capabilities for "
"handling 3D graphics more efficiently than a CPU (central processing unit)."
msgstr ""
"Unit pemrosesan grafis. Sebuah mikroprosesor dengan kemampuan bawaan untuk "
"menangani grafis 3D lebih efisien daripada CPU (unit pemrosesan pusat)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:208
msgid "Gravity:"
msgstr "Gravity:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:209
msgid ""
"Gravity in OpenShot is a property of each clip that sets the clip's initial "
"position on the screen."
msgstr ""
"Gravity di OpenShot adalah properti dari setiap klip yang mengatur posisi "
"awal klip di layar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:210
msgid "Green screen"
msgstr "Layar hijau"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:211
msgid ""
"A green background that the subject stands in front of that is another "
"background in post-production."
msgstr ""
"Latar belakang hijau yang menjadi tempat subjek berdiri dan digantikan "
"dengan latar belakang lain dalam pasca-produksi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:213
msgid "Green Screen Compositing"
msgstr "Komposit Layar Hijau"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:213
msgid ""
"The process of making all green elements in an image transparent and placing "
"a different background underneath, so it appears that the subject is in a "
"different location."
msgstr ""
"Proses membuat semua elemen hijau dalam gambar menjadi transparan dan "
"menempatkan latar belakang berbeda di bawahnya, sehingga tampak bahwa subjek "
"berada di lokasi yang berbeda."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:218
msgid "-H-"
msgstr "-H-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:219
msgid "High Definition (HD):"
msgstr "Definisi Tinggi (HD):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:220
msgid ""
"A general term for a video signal with a significantly higher resolution "
"than standard definition."
msgstr ""
"Istilah umum untuk sinyal video dengan resolusi yang jauh lebih tinggi "
"daripada definisi standar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:221
msgid "HDMI:"
msgstr "HDMI:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:222
msgid ""
"High Definition Multimedia Interface.  Interface for transmitting high "
"definition digital audio and video data."
msgstr ""
"High Definition Multimedia Interface. Antarmuka untuk mentransmisikan data "
"audio dan video digital definisi tinggi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:223
msgid "HDR:"
msgstr "HDR:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:224
msgid ""
"HDR (high dynamic range) is the compositing of two images, one that "
"correctly exposes the highlights, and another that properly exposes the dark "
"areas.  When composited together, you get a properly exposed image."
msgstr ""
"HDR (high dynamic range) adalah penggabungan dua gambar, satu yang "
"mengekspos highlight dengan benar, dan satu lagi yang mengekspos area gelap "
"dengan tepat. Ketika digabungkan, Anda mendapatkan gambar dengan eksposur "
"yang tepat."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:225
msgid "HDTV:"
msgstr "HDTV:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:226
msgid ""
"High Definition TV.  A broadcast format that allows for a higher resolution "
"signal than the traditional formats, NTSC, PAL, and SECAM."
msgstr ""
"High Definition TV. Format siaran yang memungkinkan sinyal dengan resolusi "
"lebih tinggi daripada format tradisional, NTSC, PAL, dan SECAM."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:227
msgid "HDV:"
msgstr "HDV:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:228
msgid ""
"High Definition Video.  The format used to record HDTV-quality data with "
"video camcorders."
msgstr ""
"High Definition Video. Format yang digunakan untuk merekam data kualitas "
"HDTV dengan kamera video."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:229
msgid "Headroom:"
msgstr "Headroom:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:230
msgid ""
"The space between the top of a character's head and the top of the frame."
msgstr "Ruang antara bagian atas kepala karakter dan bagian atas frame."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:231
msgid "Hiss:"
msgstr "Hiss:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:232
msgid "Noise caused by imperfections in the recording medium."
msgstr ""
"Suara bising yang disebabkan oleh ketidaksempurnaan pada media rekaman."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:234
msgid "Hue:"
msgstr "Hue:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:234
msgid ""
"The shade of a color.  This is the general color category into which the "
"color falls.  For example, pink, crimson, and plum are different colors, but "
"they all fall under the hue of red.  White, black, and gray tones are not "
"hues."
msgstr ""
"Bayangan warna. Ini adalah kategori warna umum tempat warna tersebut masuk. "
"Misalnya, merah muda, merah tua, dan plum adalah warna yang berbeda, tetapi "
"semuanya termasuk dalam rona merah. Putih, hitam, dan abu-abu bukanlah rona."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:239
msgid "-I-"
msgstr "-I-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:240
msgid "Image Stabilizer:"
msgstr "Penstabil Gambar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:241
msgid ""
"Also referred to as an electronic image stabilizer.  A technique used to "
"remove the movement caused by camera shake."
msgstr ""
"Juga disebut sebagai penstabil gambar elektronik. Teknik yang digunakan "
"untuk menghilangkan gerakan yang disebabkan oleh guncangan kamera."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:242
msgid "Importing:"
msgstr "Impor:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:243
msgid ""
"Importing is the process of transferring videos from your camera onto your "
"computer or into a piece of editing software."
msgstr ""
"Impor adalah proses memindahkan video dari kamera Anda ke komputer atau ke "
"perangkat lunak pengeditan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:244
msgid "Interframe Compression:"
msgstr "Kompresi Antarframe:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:245
msgid ""
"A compression scheme, such as MPEG that reduces the amount of video "
"information by storing only the differences between a frame and those "
"preceding it."
msgstr ""
"Skema kompresi, seperti MPEG, yang mengurangi jumlah informasi video dengan "
"menyimpan hanya perbedaan antara sebuah frame dan frame sebelumnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:246
msgid "Interpolation:"
msgstr "Interpolasi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:247
msgid ""
"Used in animation to calculate the motion in between two user-generated "
"keyframes so that the editor does not need to animate each frame manually.  "
"This speeds up the process and makes the resulting animation smoother."
msgstr ""
"Digunakan dalam animasi untuk menghitung gerakan di antara dua keyframe yang "
"dibuat pengguna sehingga editor tidak perlu menganimasikan setiap frame "
"secara manual. Ini mempercepat proses dan membuat animasi yang dihasilkan "
"lebih halus."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:249
msgid "Intertitles:"
msgstr "Intertitel:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:249
msgid ""
"Titles that appear on their own between footage.  Commonly seen in silent "
"movies to substitute dialogue, also used as chapter headings."
msgstr ""
"Judul yang muncul sendiri di antara rekaman. Umumnya terlihat dalam film "
"bisu sebagai pengganti dialog, juga digunakan sebagai judul bab."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:254
msgid "-J-"
msgstr "-J-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:255
msgid "J-Cut:"
msgstr "J-Cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:256
msgid ""
"An edit in which the audio starts before the video, giving the video a "
"dramatic introduction.  Also known as an audio lead."
msgstr ""
"Suntingan di mana audio dimulai sebelum video, memberikan pengantar dramatis "
"pada video. Juga dikenal sebagai audio lead."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:257
msgid "Jog"
msgstr "Jog"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:258
msgid ""
"To move forward or backward through video by playing it one field or frame "
"at a time."
msgstr ""
"Bergerak maju atau mundur melalui video dengan memutarnya satu bidang atau "
"frame pada satu waktu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:260
msgid "Jump Cut:"
msgstr "Jump Cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:260
msgid ""
"A jump cut is an unnatural, abrupt switch between shots identical in the "
"subject but slightly different in screen location, so the subject appears to "
"jump from one screen location to another."
msgstr ""
"Jump cut adalah perpindahan yang tidak alami dan tiba-tiba antara adegan "
"yang subjeknya sama tetapi sedikit berbeda lokasi di layar, sehingga subjek "
"tampak melompat dari satu lokasi layar ke lokasi lain."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:265
msgid "-K-"
msgstr "-K-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:266
msgid "Key:"
msgstr "Key:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:267
msgid ""
"A method for creating transparency, such as a bluescreen key or a chroma key."
msgstr ""
"Metode untuk membuat transparansi, seperti key bluescreen atau chroma key."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:269
msgid "Keyframe:"
msgstr "Keyframe:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:269
msgid ""
"A keyframe is a frame that contains a record of specific settings (e.g., "
"scale, rotation, brightness).  Start and endpoints for animated effects.  By "
"setting multiple keyframes, you can adjust these parameters as the video "
"plays to animate certain aspects."
msgstr ""
"Keyframe adalah frame yang berisi catatan pengaturan tertentu (misalnya, "
"skala, rotasi, kecerahan). Titik awal dan akhir untuk efek animasi. Dengan "
"mengatur beberapa keyframe, Anda dapat menyesuaikan parameter ini saat video "
"diputar untuk menganimasikan aspek tertentu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:274
msgid "-L-"
msgstr "-L-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:275
msgid "L-Cut:"
msgstr "L-Cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:276
msgid ""
"An L-cut is an edit in which the video ends before the audio.  L-cuts act as "
"a subtle transition from one scene to the next."
msgstr ""
"L-cut adalah suntingan di mana video berakhir sebelum audio. L-cut berfungsi "
"sebagai transisi halus dari satu adegan ke adegan berikutnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:277
msgid "Letterbox:"
msgstr "Letterbox:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:278
msgid ""
"A technique used to preserve the original aspect ratio of a motion picture "
"when played on a TV.  Letterboxing adds black bars to the top and bottom of "
"the screen."
msgstr ""
"Teknik yang digunakan untuk mempertahankan rasio aspek asli film saat "
"diputar di TV. Letterboxing menambahkan bilah hitam di bagian atas dan bawah "
"layar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:279
msgid "Linear Editing:"
msgstr "Penyuntingan Linear:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:280
msgid ""
"A form of video editing which lays out cuts sequentially, one by one, to "
"produce the final scene. This contrasts with non-linear editing which allows "
"cutting in any order."
msgstr ""
"Bentuk penyuntingan video yang menyusun potongan secara berurutan, satu per "
"satu, untuk menghasilkan adegan akhir. Ini berbeda dengan penyuntingan non-"
"linear yang memungkinkan pemotongan dalam urutan apa pun."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:281
msgid "Log:"
msgstr "Log:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:282
msgid ""
"A record of start and end timecode, reel numbers, scene descriptions, and "
"other information for a specified clip."
msgstr ""
"Catatan kode waktu mulai dan akhir, nomor gulungan, deskripsi adegan, dan "
"informasi lain untuk klip tertentu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:283
msgid "Lossless:"
msgstr "Lossless:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:284
msgid ""
"A compression scheme that results in no loss of data from decompressing the "
"file.  Lossless files are generally quite large (but still smaller than "
"uncompressed versions) and sometimes require considerable processing power "
"to decode the data."
msgstr ""
"Skema kompresi yang tidak menyebabkan kehilangan data saat file "
"didekompresi. File lossless umumnya cukup besar (tetapi masih lebih kecil "
"dari versi tidak terkompresi) dan terkadang memerlukan daya pemrosesan yang "
"cukup besar untuk mendekode data."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:286
msgid "Lossy:"
msgstr "Lossy:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:286
msgid ""
"Lossy compression is a compression scheme that degrades quality.  Lossy "
"algorithms compress digital data by eliminating the data least sensitive to "
"the human eye and offer the highest compression rates available."
msgstr ""
"Kompresi lossy adalah skema kompresi yang menurunkan kualitas. Algoritma "
"lossy mengompresi data digital dengan menghilangkan data yang paling tidak "
"sensitif terhadap mata manusia dan menawarkan tingkat kompresi tertinggi "
"yang tersedia."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:291
msgid "-M-"
msgstr "-M-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:292
msgid "Mark In:"
msgstr "Tandai Masuk:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:293
msgid "Placing a marker at the beginning of where you want your clip to start."
msgstr "Menempatkan penanda di awal tempat Anda ingin klip dimulai."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:294
msgid "Mark Out:"
msgstr "Tandai Keluar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:295
msgid "Placing a marker at the beginning of where you want your clip to end."
msgstr "Menempatkan penanda di awal tempat Anda ingin klip berakhir."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:296
msgid "Match Action:"
msgstr "Match Action:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:297
msgid ""
"Match action (or match cut) is a technique where an editor will cut from one "
"visually similar scene to another."
msgstr ""
"Match action (atau match cut) adalah teknik di mana editor memotong dari "
"satu adegan yang secara visual mirip ke adegan lain."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:298
msgid "Memory Bank:"
msgstr "Memory Bank:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:299
msgid ""
"A Memory Bank is a video that documents specific periods or events in "
"someone's life.  It can be set to music, make use of natural sound, record "
"vacations, or just capture moments in everyday life."
msgstr ""
"Memory Bank adalah video yang mendokumentasikan periode atau peristiwa "
"tertentu dalam kehidupan seseorang. Bisa disetel dengan musik, menggunakan "
"suara alami, merekam liburan, atau hanya menangkap momen dalam kehidupan "
"sehari-hari."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:300
msgid "Marker:"
msgstr "Penanda:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:301
msgid ""
"An object used to mark a location.  Clip markers signify essential points "
"within a clip.  Timeline markers indicate scenes, locations for titles, or "
"other significant points within an entire movie.  Use clip markers and "
"timeline markers for positioning and trimming clips."
msgstr ""
"Objek yang digunakan untuk menandai lokasi. Penanda klip menandai titik "
"penting dalam sebuah klip. Penanda timeline menunjukkan adegan, lokasi untuk "
"judul, atau titik penting lain dalam keseluruhan film. Gunakan penanda klip "
"dan timeline untuk penempatan dan pemotongan klip."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:302
msgid "Mask:"
msgstr "Masker:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:303
msgid ""
"The transparent area of an image, typically defined by a graphic shape or a "
"bluescreen background.  Also called a matte."
msgstr ""
"Area transparan dari sebuah gambar, biasanya didefinisikan oleh bentuk "
"grafis atau latar belakang bluescreen. Juga disebut matte."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:304
msgid "Matte:"
msgstr "Matte:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:305
msgid ""
"Matte is an image mask used in visual effects to control applying an effect "
"to certain parts of the image."
msgstr ""
"Matte adalah masker gambar yang digunakan dalam efek visual untuk mengontrol "
"penerapan efek pada bagian tertentu dari gambar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:306
msgid "Montage:"
msgstr "Montase:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:307
msgid ""
"A montage is a self-contained sequence of shots assembled in juxtaposition "
"to each other to communicate an idea or mood.  The implied relationship "
"between seemingly unrelated material creates a new message."
msgstr ""
"Montase adalah rangkaian adegan yang berdiri sendiri yang disusun "
"bersebelahan untuk menyampaikan ide atau suasana. Hubungan tersirat antara "
"materi yang tampaknya tidak terkait menciptakan pesan baru."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:309
msgid "Motion Artifact:"
msgstr "Artefak Gerak:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:309
msgid ""
"Visual interference caused by the difference between the frame rate of the "
"camera and the motion of the object.  The most common display of this is "
"when filming a computer or television screen.  The screen flickers or a line "
"scans down it, which is the difference in frame rates and a lack of "
"synchronization between the camera and television."
msgstr ""
"Gangguan visual yang disebabkan oleh perbedaan antara kecepatan bingkai "
"kamera dan gerakan objek. Tampilan paling umum dari ini adalah saat merekam "
"layar komputer atau televisi. Layar berkedip atau garis memindai ke bawah, "
"yang merupakan perbedaan kecepatan bingkai dan kurangnya sinkronisasi antara "
"kamera dan televisi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:314
msgid "-N-"
msgstr "-N-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:315
msgid "Noise:"
msgstr "Noise:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:316
msgid "Undesired data in a video or audio signal.  See also artifact."
msgstr ""
"Data yang tidak diinginkan dalam sinyal video atau audio. Lihat juga artefak."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:317
msgid "Non-linear Editing:"
msgstr "Penyuntingan Non-linear:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:318
msgid ""
"An editing system that performs edits at any time, in any order.  Access is "
"random, which means that the system can jump to specific pieces of data "
"without having to look through the whole footage to find it."
msgstr ""
"Sistem penyuntingan yang melakukan penyuntingan kapan saja, dalam urutan apa "
"pun. Aksesnya acak, yang berarti sistem dapat langsung menuju bagian data "
"tertentu tanpa harus melihat seluruh rekaman untuk menemukannya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:319
msgid "Numerator:"
msgstr "Pembilang:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:320
msgid "The number or expression above the line in a fraction (such as 1 in ½)."
msgstr ""
"Angka atau ekspresi di atas garis dalam sebuah pecahan (seperti 1 dalam ½)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:322
msgid "NTSC:"
msgstr "NTSC:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:322
msgid ""
"NTSC is an abbreviation for National Television Standards Committee.  NTSC "
"is the group that initially developed the black & white and subsequently "
"color television system.  The United States, Japan, and many other countries "
"use NTSC.  Five-hundred twenty-five interlaced lines make up NTSC that "
"display at a rate of 29.97 frames per second.  ATSC Has now superseded by "
"NTSC."
msgstr ""
"NTSC adalah singkatan dari National Television Standards Committee. NTSC "
"adalah kelompok yang awalnya mengembangkan sistem televisi hitam putih dan "
"kemudian warna. Amerika Serikat, Jepang, dan banyak negara lain menggunakan "
"NTSC. NTSC terdiri dari 525 garis interlaced yang ditampilkan dengan "
"kecepatan 29,97 bingkai per detik. ATSC kini telah menggantikan NTSC."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:327
msgid "-O-"
msgstr "-O-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:328
msgid "Offline Editing:"
msgstr "Penyuntingan Offline:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:329
msgid ""
"Editing a rough cut using low-quality clips, and then producing the final "
"cut with high-quality clips, usually on a more sophisticated editing system "
"than that used for developing the rough."
msgstr ""
"Menyunting potongan kasar menggunakan klip berkualitas rendah, lalu "
"menghasilkan potongan akhir dengan klip berkualitas tinggi, biasanya pada "
"sistem penyuntingan yang lebih canggih daripada yang digunakan untuk membuat "
"potongan kasar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:330
msgid "Online Editing:"
msgstr "Penyuntingan Online:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:331
msgid ""
"Doing all editing (including the rough cut) on the same clips that produce "
"the final cut."
msgstr ""
"Melakukan semua penyuntingan (termasuk potongan kasar) pada klip yang sama "
"yang menghasilkan potongan akhir."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:333
msgid "Opacity:"
msgstr "Opasitas:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:333
msgid ""
"An inverse measure of the level of transparency in an image, which is of "
"importance when compositing.  An image's alpha channel stores its opacity "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Ukuran kebalikan dari tingkat transparansi dalam sebuah gambar, yang penting "
"saat komposit. Saluran alfa gambar menyimpan informasi opasitasnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:338
msgid "-P-"
msgstr "-P-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:339
msgid "PAL:"
msgstr "PAL:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:340
msgid ""
"PAL is an abbreviation for Phase Alternate Line.  This is the video format "
"standard used in many European countries.  Six-hundred twenty-five lines "
"make up a PAL picture that displays at a rate of 25 frames per second."
msgstr ""
"PAL adalah singkatan dari Phase Alternate Line. Ini adalah standar format "
"video yang digunakan di banyak negara Eropa. Gambar PAL terdiri dari 625 "
"garis yang ditampilkan dengan kecepatan 25 bingkai per detik."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:341
msgid "Pan:"
msgstr "Pan:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:342
msgid "A horizontal movement of the camera on a fixed axis."
msgstr "Gerakan horizontal kamera pada sumbu tetap."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:343
msgid "Pan and Scan:"
msgstr "Pan dan Scan:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:344
msgid ""
"A method of converting widescreen images to a 4:3 aspect ratio.  Cropping "
"the video so that it fills the entire screen and panning it into position "
"shows the essential parts of the scene."
msgstr ""
"Metode mengubah gambar layar lebar menjadi rasio aspek 4:3. Memotong video "
"agar memenuhi seluruh layar dan menggesernya ke posisi yang menunjukkan "
"bagian penting dari adegan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:345
msgid "Picture in Picture (PIP):"
msgstr "Picture in Picture (PIP):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:346
msgid ""
"An effect of superimposing a small window of footage over a larger window "
"and the two play at the same time."
msgstr ""
"Efek menumpuk jendela kecil rekaman di atas jendela yang lebih besar dan "
"keduanya diputar bersamaan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:347
msgid "Pixel:"
msgstr "Piksel:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:348
msgid ""
"One of the tiny dots that make up the representation of an image in a "
"computer's memory.  The smallest unit of a digital image."
msgstr ""
"Salah satu titik kecil yang membentuk representasi gambar dalam memori "
"komputer. Unit terkecil dari gambar digital."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:349
msgid "Pixel Aspect Ratio:"
msgstr "Rasio Aspek Piksel:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:350
msgid ""
"Aspect ratio is the ratio between the width and height of your video; the "
"Pixel Aspect Ratio is the ratio between the width and height of the pixels.  "
"A standard Pixel Aspect Ratio is 1:1."
msgstr ""
"Rasio aspek adalah perbandingan antara lebar dan tinggi video Anda; Rasio "
"Aspek Piksel adalah perbandingan antara lebar dan tinggi piksel. Rasio Aspek "
"Piksel standar adalah 1:1."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:351
msgid "Pixelation:"
msgstr "Pikselasi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:352
msgid ""
"The display of large, blocky pixels in an image caused by over-enlarging it."
msgstr ""
"Tampilan piksel besar dan kotak-kotak dalam gambar yang disebabkan oleh "
"pembesaran berlebihan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:353
msgid "Playhead:"
msgstr "Playhead:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:354
msgid ""
"When editing audio or video in a current computer, the Playhead is a graphic "
"line in the Timeline that represents the current accessed position, or "
"frame, of the material."
msgstr ""
"Saat menyunting audio atau video di komputer saat ini, Playhead adalah garis "
"grafis di Timeline yang mewakili posisi atau bingkai yang sedang diakses "
"dari materi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:355
msgid "Post-production (Post):"
msgstr "Pasca-produksi (Pasca):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:356
msgid ""
"Post-production (post) is any video production activity following the "
"initial recording.  Typically, post involves editing, the addition of "
"background music, voice-over, sound effects, titles, and various visual "
"effects resulting in completed production."
msgstr ""
"Pasca-produksi adalah aktivitas produksi video apa pun setelah rekaman awal. "
"Biasanya, pasca melibatkan penyuntingan, penambahan musik latar, sulih "
"suara, efek suara, judul, dan berbagai efek visual yang menghasilkan "
"produksi selesai."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:357
msgid "Poster Frame:"
msgstr "Frame Poster:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:358
msgid ""
"A single frame of a clip, selected as a thumbnail to indicate the clip's "
"contents."
msgstr ""
"Satu bingkai dari klip, dipilih sebagai thumbnail untuk menunjukkan isi klip."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:360
msgid "Project:"
msgstr "Proyek:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:360
msgid ""
"A project is all the files, transitions, effects, and animations that you "
"make or use within OpenShot."
msgstr ""
"Proyek adalah semua file, transisi, efek, dan animasi yang Anda buat atau "
"gunakan dalam OpenShot."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:365
msgid "-R-"
msgstr "-R-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:366
msgid "Raw Footage:"
msgstr "Rekaman Mentah:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:367
msgid "Raw footage is pre-edited footage, usually direct from the camera."
msgstr ""
"Rekaman mentah adalah rekaman yang belum diedit, biasanya langsung dari "
"kamera."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:368
msgid "Real-time:"
msgstr "Waktu nyata:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:369
msgid ""
"Real-time occurs immediately, without delay for rendering.  If a transition "
"occurs in real-time, there is no waiting, the computer creates the effect or "
"transition on-the-fly, showing it the results immediately."
msgstr ""
"Waktu nyata terjadi segera, tanpa penundaan untuk rendering. Jika sebuah "
"transisi terjadi secara waktu nyata, tidak ada penantian, komputer membuat "
"efek atau transisi secara langsung, menampilkan hasilnya segera."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:370
msgid "Rendering:"
msgstr "Rendering:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:371
msgid ""
"The process by which the video editing software and hardware convert the raw "
"video, effects, transitions, and filters into a new continuous video file."
msgstr ""
"Proses di mana perangkat lunak dan perangkat keras pengedit video mengubah "
"video mentah, efek, transisi, dan filter menjadi file video baru yang "
"berkelanjutan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:372
msgid "Render Time:"
msgstr "Waktu Render:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:373
msgid ""
"The render time is the time it takes an editing computer to composite source "
"elements and commands into a single video file.  Rendering allows the "
"sequence, including titles and transition effects, to play in full motion."
msgstr ""
"Waktu render adalah waktu yang dibutuhkan komputer pengedit untuk "
"menggabungkan elemen sumber dan perintah menjadi satu file video. Rendering "
"memungkinkan urutan, termasuk judul dan efek transisi, diputar dengan "
"gerakan penuh."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:374
msgid "Resolution:"
msgstr "Resolusi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:375
msgid ""
"Resolution refers to the actual number of horizontal and vertical pixels "
"your video contains.  Common resolution Examples: (SD) 640×480, (HD) "
"854x480, (HD) 1280×720, (FHD) 1920×1080, (QHD) 2560x1440, (UHD) 3840x2160, "
"and (FUHD) 7680x4320.  Often the numbers that appear vertically refer to the "
"resolution.  The examples listed would appear as SD, 480p, 720p, 1080p, "
"1440p, 4K and 8K, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Resolusi mengacu pada jumlah sebenarnya piksel horizontal dan vertikal yang "
"dimiliki video Anda. Contoh resolusi umum: (SD) 640×480, (HD) 854x480, (HD) "
"1280×720, (FHD) 1920×1080, (QHD) 2560x1440, (UHD) 3840x2160, dan (FUHD) "
"7680x4320. Seringkali angka yang muncul secara vertikal merujuk pada "
"resolusi. Contoh yang tercantum akan muncul sebagai SD, 480p, 720p, 1080p, "
"1440p, 4K, dan 8K, masing-masing."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:376
msgid "RGB:"
msgstr "RGB:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:377
msgid ""
"Monitors, cameras, and digital projectors use the primary colors of light "
"(Red, Green, and Blue) to make images."
msgstr ""
"Monitor, kamera, dan proyektor digital menggunakan warna primer cahaya "
"(Merah, Hijau, dan Biru) untuk membuat gambar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:378
msgid "RGBA:"
msgstr "RGBA:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:379
msgid ""
"A file containing an RGB image plus an alpha channel for transparency "
"information."
msgstr ""
"File yang berisi gambar RGB plus saluran alfa untuk informasi transparansi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:380
msgid "Roll:"
msgstr "Roll:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:381
msgid ""
"Roll is a text effect commonly seen in end credits, where text typically "
"moves from the bottom to the top of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Roll adalah efek teks yang umum terlihat di kredit akhir, di mana teks "
"biasanya bergerak dari bawah ke atas layar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:383
msgid "Rough cut:"
msgstr "Rough cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:383
msgid ""
"A rough cut is a preliminary edit of footage in the approximate sequence, "
"length, and content of a finished program."
msgstr ""
"Rough cut adalah penyuntingan awal rekaman dalam urutan, panjang, dan isi "
"yang kira-kira sesuai dengan program jadi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:388
msgid "-S-"
msgstr "-S-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:389
msgid "Sample Rate:"
msgstr "Sample Rate:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:390
msgid ""
"In digital audio, the number of samples per second.  The higher the number, "
"the better the sound quality."
msgstr ""
"Dalam audio digital, jumlah sampel per detik. Semakin tinggi angkanya, "
"semakin baik kualitas suara."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:391
msgid "Scene:"
msgstr "Adegan:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:392
msgid "Action that occurs in one location at one time."
msgstr "Aksi yang terjadi di satu lokasi pada satu waktu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:393
msgid "Scrub:"
msgstr "Scrub:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:394
msgid ""
"Scrubbing is an act of moving the cursor or playhead across the Timeline "
"manually.  Once specific to audio tracks, the term now also refers to video "
"tracks."
msgstr ""
"Scrubbing adalah tindakan menggerakkan kursor atau playhead secara manual di "
"sepanjang Timeline. Awalnya khusus untuk trek audio, istilah ini sekarang "
"juga merujuk pada trek video."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:395
msgid "Shot:"
msgstr "Shot:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:396
msgid "A recording of a single take."
msgstr "Rekaman dari satu pengambilan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:397
msgid "Side Data:"
msgstr "Side Data:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:398
msgid ""
"Auxiliary per-stream metadata (e.g. rotation, stereo3D, spherical) attached "
"to packets or streams in containers like MP4."
msgstr ""
"Metadata tambahan per aliran (misalnya rotasi, stereo3D, spherical) yang "
"terpasang pada paket atau aliran dalam kontainer seperti MP4."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:399
msgid "Slow-motion:"
msgstr "Slow-motion:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:400
msgid ""
"A shot in which action takes place at a slower than average speed.  The "
"camera achieves slow-motion by speeding up the frame rate during recording "
"and then playing back the frames at a slower speed."
msgstr ""
"Sebuah shot di mana aksi berlangsung dengan kecepatan lebih lambat dari rata-"
"rata. Kamera mencapai slow-motion dengan mempercepat frame rate saat merekam "
"dan kemudian memutar ulang frame dengan kecepatan lebih lambat."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:401
msgid "Snap:"
msgstr "Snap:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:402
msgid ""
"Snapping quickly positions an object in alignment with grid lines, "
"guidelines, or another object.  Snapping causes the object to automatically "
"jump to an exact position when the user drags it to the proximity of the "
"desired location."
msgstr ""
"Snapping dengan cepat menempatkan objek sejajar dengan garis kisi, panduan, "
"atau objek lain. Snapping menyebabkan objek secara otomatis melompat ke "
"posisi tepat saat pengguna menyeretnya ke dekat lokasi yang diinginkan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:403
msgid "Spherical Video:"
msgstr "Video Spherical:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:404
msgid ""
"A full-sphere (360×180°) video format that requires special metadata (SV3D) "
"so players know to render it as an interactive panorama."
msgstr ""
"Format video bola penuh (360×180°) yang memerlukan metadata khusus (SV3D) "
"agar pemutar tahu untuk merendernya sebagai panorama interaktif."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:405
msgid "Splice:"
msgstr "Splice:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:406
msgid ""
"The process of physically attaching two pieces of film using tape or cement."
msgstr ""
"Proses menggabungkan dua potong film secara fisik menggunakan pita atau "
"semen."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:407
msgid "Split cut (L-cut or J-cut):"
msgstr "Split cut (L-cut atau J-cut):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:408
msgid ""
"An edit in which the audio starts before or after the picture cut.  Used for "
"easing the transition from one scene or shot to another."
msgstr ""
"Sebuah penyuntingan di mana audio dimulai sebelum atau setelah potongan "
"gambar. Digunakan untuk mempermudah transisi dari satu adegan atau shot ke "
"yang lain."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:409
msgid "Splitscreen:"
msgstr "Splitscreen:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:410
msgid ""
"A unique effect that displays two or more scenes simultaneously on different "
"parts of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Efek unik yang menampilkan dua atau lebih adegan secara bersamaan di bagian "
"layar yang berbeda."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:411
msgid "Sound Effects:"
msgstr "Efek Suara:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:412
msgid ""
"Sound effects are contrived audio, usually prerecorded, incorporated with a "
"video soundtrack to resemble a real occurrence.  Blowing on a microphone, "
"for example, might simulate wind to accompany hurricane images."
msgstr ""
"Efek suara adalah audio yang dibuat-buat, biasanya direkam sebelumnya, "
"digabungkan dengan soundtrack video untuk menyerupai kejadian nyata. "
"Misalnya, meniup mikrofon dapat mensimulasikan angin untuk menemani gambar "
"badai."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:413
msgid "Soundtrack:"
msgstr "Soundtrack:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:414
msgid ""
"The soundtrack is the audio portion of a video recording, often multifaceted "
"with natural sound, voiceovers, background music, or other sounds."
msgstr ""
"Soundtrack adalah bagian audio dari rekaman video, seringkali multifaset "
"dengan suara alami, sulih suara, musik latar, atau suara lainnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:415
msgid "Stabilization:"
msgstr "Stabilisasi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:416
msgid ""
"Image stabilization is a family of techniques that reduce blurring "
"associated with the motion of a camera or other imaging device during "
"exposure."
msgstr ""
"Stabilisasi gambar adalah sekumpulan teknik yang mengurangi blur yang "
"terkait dengan gerakan kamera atau perangkat pencitraan lain selama eksposur."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:417
msgid "Standard Definition (SD):"
msgstr "Definisi Standar (SD):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:418
msgid ""
"Television broadcasting standard with a lower resolution than high "
"definition."
msgstr ""
"Standar siaran televisi dengan resolusi lebih rendah daripada definisi "
"tinggi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:419
msgid "Step:"
msgstr "Langkah:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:420
msgid ""
"The act of moving forward or backward through video one frame at a time."
msgstr ""
"Tindakan bergerak maju atau mundur melalui video satu frame pada satu waktu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:421
msgid "Still Frame:"
msgstr "Still Frame:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:422
msgid "A single frame of video is repeated, so it appears to have no motion."
msgstr "Satu frame video diulang, sehingga tampak tidak bergerak."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:423
msgid "Straight Cut:"
msgstr "Straight Cut:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:424
msgid ""
"The most common edit, consecutive clips placed one after another in the "
"Timeline window.  Straight cuts are preferable to transitions when the "
"scenes are similar, and you do not want edits to be noticeable."
msgstr ""
"Edit yang paling umum, klip berurutan ditempatkan satu setelah yang lain di "
"jendela Timeline. Potongan lurus lebih disukai daripada transisi ketika "
"adegan serupa, dan Anda tidak ingin edit terlihat."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:425
msgid "Superimposing:"
msgstr "Superimposisi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:426
msgid "Combining images, where one or more layers involve transparency."
msgstr ""
"Menggabungkan gambar, di mana satu atau lebih lapisan melibatkan "
"transparansi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:427
msgid "Sync (Synchronization):"
msgstr "Sinkronisasi (Sinkronisasi):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:428
msgid ""
"Synchronization refers to the relative timing of audio (sound) and video "
"(image) parts during creation, post-production (mixing), transmission, "
"reception, and play-back processing."
msgstr ""
"Sinkronisasi mengacu pada waktu relatif antara bagian audio (suara) dan "
"video (gambar) selama pembuatan, pasca-produksi (mixing), transmisi, "
"penerimaan, dan pemrosesan pemutaran."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:429
msgid "SECAM:"
msgstr "SECAM:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:430
msgid ""
"Systeme Electronique Couleur Avec Memoire, a TV format used mainly in "
"Eastern Europe, Russia, and Africa."
msgstr ""
"Systeme Electronique Couleur Avec Memoire, format TV yang digunakan terutama "
"di Eropa Timur, Rusia, dan Afrika."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:432
msgid "SV3D (Spherical Video metadata):"
msgstr "SV3D (Metadata Video Sferis):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:432
msgid ""
"The “sv3d” atom in MP4/MOV files—side-data that marks a clip as 360° and "
"carries projection, yaw/pitch/roll parameters."
msgstr ""
"Atom “sv3d” dalam file MP4/MOV—data samping yang menandai klip sebagai 360° "
"dan membawa parameter proyeksi, yaw/pitch/roll."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:437
msgid "-T-"
msgstr "-T-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:438
msgid "Tilt:"
msgstr "Miring:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:439
msgid ""
"Tilting is a cinematographic technique in which the camera stays in a fixed "
"position but rotates up/down in a vertical plane."
msgstr ""
"Miring adalah teknik sinematografi di mana kamera tetap pada posisi tetap "
"tetapi berputar ke atas/bawah pada bidang vertikal."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:440
msgid "Timecode:"
msgstr "Timecode:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:441
msgid ""
"The timecode is the discrete address given to each frame of the video (for "
"example, 1:20:24:09).  Timecode makes frame-accurate editing possible and "
"allows editors to identify scenes precisely in a log."
msgstr ""
"Timecode adalah alamat diskrit yang diberikan ke setiap frame video "
"(misalnya, 1:20:24:09). Timecode memungkinkan pengeditan yang akurat per "
"frame dan memungkinkan editor mengidentifikasi adegan dengan tepat dalam log."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:442
msgid "Time-lapse:"
msgstr "Time-lapse:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:443
msgid ""
"It is a technique for capturing each frame in a video at a much slower rate "
"than usual.  When played back at regular speed, time appears to go by "
"faster.  An editing program achieves this by fast-forwarding or increasing "
"the speed of your video."
msgstr ""
"Ini adalah teknik untuk menangkap setiap frame dalam video dengan kecepatan "
"jauh lebih lambat dari biasanya. Saat diputar kembali dengan kecepatan "
"normal, waktu tampak berjalan lebih cepat. Program pengeditan mencapainya "
"dengan memajukan cepat atau meningkatkan kecepatan video Anda."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:444
msgid "Timeline:"
msgstr "Timeline:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:445
msgid ""
"The Timeline is an editing interface that lays out a video project in a "
"linear fashion consisting of clips laid horizontally across the screen."
msgstr ""
"Timeline adalah antarmuka pengeditan yang menyusun proyek video secara "
"linear yang terdiri dari klip yang ditempatkan secara horizontal di layar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:446
msgid "Timeline Editing:"
msgstr "Pengeditan Timeline:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:447
msgid ""
"Timeline editing is a computer-based method of editing, in which bars "
"proportional to the length of a clip, represent video and audio clips on a "
"computer screen."
msgstr ""
"Pengeditan timeline adalah metode pengeditan berbasis komputer, di mana "
"batang yang proporsional dengan panjang klip mewakili klip video dan audio "
"di layar komputer."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:448
msgid "Titling:"
msgstr "Penambahan Judul:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:449
msgid ""
"Titling is the process or result of incorporating on-screen text as credits, "
"captions, or any other alphanumeric communication."
msgstr ""
"Penambahan judul adalah proses atau hasil memasukkan teks di layar sebagai "
"kredit, keterangan, atau komunikasi alfanumerik lainnya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:450
msgid "Track:"
msgstr "Track:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:451
msgid "A separate audio or video layer on a timeline."
msgstr "Lapisan audio atau video terpisah pada timeline."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:452
msgid "Transcode:"
msgstr "Transkode:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:453
msgid ""
"Converting a digital file to another digital file format.  This usually "
"involves audio and video compression."
msgstr ""
"Mengonversi file digital ke format file digital lain. Ini biasanya "
"melibatkan kompresi audio dan video."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:454
msgid "Transparency:"
msgstr "Transparansi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:455
msgid "Percentage of the opacity of a video clip or element."
msgstr "Persentase opasitas klip video atau elemen."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:456
msgid "Transition:"
msgstr "Transisi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:457
msgid ""
"A method of juxtaposing two scenes.  Transitions can take many forms, "
"including cuts, dissolves, and wipes."
msgstr ""
"Metode menempatkan dua adegan berdampingan. Transisi dapat berbentuk "
"potongan, larut, dan sapuan."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:459
msgid "Trim:"
msgstr "Potong:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:459
msgid "Removing frames from the beginning, middle, or end of a clip."
msgstr "Menghapus frame dari awal, tengah, atau akhir klip."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:464
msgid "-V-"
msgstr "-V-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:465
msgid "Video Format:"
msgstr "Format Video:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:466
msgid ""
"The video format is a standard that determines the way a video signal "
"records on videotape.  Standards include DV, 8-mm, Beta, and VHS."
msgstr ""
"Format video adalah standar yang menentukan cara sinyal video direkam pada "
"pita video. Standar termasuk DV, 8-mm, Beta, dan VHS."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:467
msgid "Voiceover:"
msgstr "Voiceover:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:468
msgid ""
"A term used to describe off-camera narration that is not part of a scene "
"(non-diegetic)."
msgstr ""
"Istilah yang digunakan untuk menggambarkan narasi di luar kamera yang bukan "
"bagian dari adegan (non-diegetik)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:470
msgid "VTR:"
msgstr "VTR:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:470
msgid ""
"A Videotape recorder also referred to as a 'deck'.  Decks duplicate "
"videotapes and inputting and outputting from a computer."
msgstr ""
"Perekam pita video yang juga disebut 'deck'. Deck menduplikasi pita video "
"dan melakukan input serta output dari komputer."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:475
msgid "-W-"
msgstr "-W-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:476
msgid "Widescreen:"
msgstr "Layar Lebar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:477
msgid ""
"A format in which the width-to-height ratio of the frame is greater than 4:3 "
"so that it is significantly wider than it is tall."
msgstr ""
"Format di mana rasio lebar terhadap tinggi bingkai lebih besar dari 4:3 "
"sehingga jauh lebih lebar daripada tingginya."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:479
msgid "Wipe:"
msgstr "Wipe:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:479
msgid ""
"A wipe is a transition from one shot to another.  The edge of the transition "
"moves across the original image as a line or a pattern, revealing the new "
"shot."
msgstr ""
"Wipe adalah transisi dari satu bidikan ke bidikan lain. Tepi transisi "
"bergerak melintasi gambar asli sebagai garis atau pola, memperlihatkan "
"bidikan baru."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:484
msgid "-Z-"
msgstr "-Z-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:486
msgid "Zoom:"
msgstr "Zoom:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:486
msgid ""
"A shot where the image grows more substantial or smaller by adjusting the "
"focal length of the lens instead of physically moving the camera."
msgstr ""
"Bidikan di mana gambar menjadi lebih besar atau lebih kecil dengan mengatur "
"panjang fokus lensa daripada memindahkan kamera secara fisik."
